<item>
            <title>[LU-15186] Default ko2iblnd map_on_demand to 1</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15186</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On kernels that provide global MR we default to using that exclusively even if FMR/FastReg is available. With &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15092&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15092&lt;/a&gt; this causes an interop issue because FMR/FastReg may be needed to map the higher fragment count. We should change the default map_on_demand to 1 so that FMR/FastReg is used by default. map_on-demand can still be set to 0 if needed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
